{"author":"Joe Oakhart","data":{"fields":{"description":"## What\n\n**Retire the band-aids** now that the ref-lock (C3) is proven, flip the default backend to `ref`,\nand remove the dead file-lock machinery + `merge=ours` entry, with a migration for existing repos.\n\n**Depends on: 2711-21bf-ab71-4136 (C3).** The ref backend must be wired and validated first;\nremoving the file backend / retry loop before C3 would leave the reconciler with no working lock.\n\n- Flip `[reconciler] lock_backend` default to `ref` and remove the `file` backend path from\n  `_advisory_lock.py` once the ref backend has baked.\n- **Remove the `b859-8fa1` retry loop** (`_advisory_lock.py:73-89, 263-291`) AND its now-dead\n  helpers: `_resolve_retry_budget` (`:114`), `_LOCK_RETRY_BUDGET_DEFAULT` (`:85`),\n  `_compute_backoff_seconds` (`:150`). Retire the config key `lock_max_retries`\n  (`_config_schema.py:334`, coercion `:445`) and its env aliases (`REBAR_RECONCILER_LOCK_MAX_RETRIES`\n  + deprecated alias). Delete/adjust the tests that exercise them:\n  `tests/unit/rebar_reconciler/state/test_advisory_lock_retry_jitter.py`, and the retry-budget\n  assertions in `tests/.../test_config_file_wiring.py` + `test_ev3c_env_renames.py`.\n- **Deprecation path for the retired config key.** `lock_max_retries` removal is operator-visible;\n  rather than a hard break, treat a still-present `lock_max_retries` as **deprecated** â€” emit a\n  one-time deprecation warning (config-load path) and ignore it â€” and note the removal in\n  `docs/config.md` + the changelog, so existing operator configs do not error on upgrade.\n- **Remove `.reconciler-*` from `_GITATTRIBUTES`** in `src/rebar/_commands/init.py:57` (leave\n  `.bridge_state/* merge=ours` at `:56` untouched â€” that is WS-1 binding data, out of scope), and\n  update `tests/interfaces/store/test_gitattributes_merge.py` to assert `.reconciler-*` is absent\n  and `.bridge_state/*` still present.\n- **Migration for already-initialized trackers:** `_commit_gitattributes` (`init.py:410`) is\n  create-if-absent only, so editing the constant does not fix existing repos. Add an update-migration\n  arm (mirroring the `_commit_gitignore` line-migration at `init.py:365-383`) that strips the\n  `.reconciler-* merge=ours` line from an already-committed `.gitattributes`. Idempotent; on git\n  failure, log-and-continue (do not abort startup).\n- **One-time cleanup:** remove any pre-existing `.reconciler-pass-lock`/`.reconciler-phase-gate`\n  committed on the tickets branch from the old scheme (a single named helper, idempotent, invoked\n  from exactly one site â€” reconciler startup; state the site explicitly).\n- Extend the ref-lock ADR to record that the b859 loop is superseded by the C3 self-healing lock.\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n\n- [ ] `lock_backend` defaults to `ref`; the file-lock backend + the `b859` retry loop\n      (`_advisory_lock.py:73-89, 263-291`) are deleted, along with `_resolve_retry_budget`,\n      `_LOCK_RETRY_BUDGET_DEFAULT`, `_compute_backoff_seconds`, the `lock_max_retries` config key\n      (`_config_schema.py:334,445`) + env aliases, and their tests.\n- [ ] `.reconciler-*` is removed from `_GITATTRIBUTES` (`init.py:57`); `.bridge_state/*` is left in\n      place; `tests/interfaces/store/test_gitattributes_merge.py` updated accordingly.\n- [ ] A `.gitattributes` update-migration (mirroring `_commit_gitignore`, `init.py:365-383`) strips\n      `.reconciler-* merge=ours` from already-committed trackers; idempotent; git failure logs and\n      continues rather than aborting.\n- [ ] A single, named, idempotent startup migration removes any pre-existing committed\n      `.reconciler-*` files; a regression test asserts no `.reconciler-*` path is ever committed to\n      the tickets branch.\n- [ ] `lock_max_retries` is handled as deprecated-and-ignored (one-time warning, not a load error)\n      and its removal is documented in `docs/config.md` + changelog.\n- [ ] Full non-integration suite green."}},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"EDIT","timestamp":1783223379541857001,"uuid":"3b0ed764-6482-4f44-8191-698bdffbfe95"}